properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 5 at 2:43PM EST until January 7 at 4:00AM EST by NWS Buffalo NY
properties.description:
* WHAT...Lake effect snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 5
to 9 inches in the most persistent lake snows. Winds gusting as
high as 35 mph may produce blowing and drifting snow on the Tug
Hill.

* WHERE...The Eastern Lake Ontario Region. Greatest snow totals on
the Tug Hill.

* WHEN...From 4 AM Monday to 4 AM EST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Lake effect snow will fall in relatively narrow bands. If
traveling, be prepared for rapidly changing road conditions and
visibilities.

Submit snow reports through our website or social media.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 AM MONDAY TO 4 AM EST TUESDAY
